==English==
===Etymology===
After Lido, a popular beach in [[Venice]] in [[Italy]].

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: ''strictly'' /ˈliːdəʊ/, ''imitating the Italian pronunciation, but commonly'' /ˈlaɪdəʊ/

===Noun===
'''lido''' (''plural'' '''lidos''')

#(''British'') An part of the sea by a beach sectioned off for swimming and other aquatic activities.
#(''British'') An outdoor swimming pool.

